com.facebook.buck.artifact_cache

Class LoggingArtifactCacheDecorator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.artifact_cache.LoggingArtifactCacheDecorator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ArtifactCache, java.lang.AutoCloseable

    public class LoggingArtifactCacheDecorator
extends java.lang.Object
implements ArtifactCache
    Decorator for wrapping a ArtifactCache to log a ArtifactCacheEvent for the start and finish of each event. The underlying cache must only provide synchronous operations.

      • store

        public ListenableFuture<java.lang.Void> store(ImmutableSet<RuleKey> ruleKeys,
                                     ImmutableMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> metadata,
                                     java.nio.file.Path output)
                                       throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Description copied from interface: ArtifactCache
        Store the artifact at path specified by output to cache, such that it can later be fetched using ruleKey as the lookup key. If any internal errors occur, fail silently and continue execution. Store may be performed synchronously or asynchronously.

        This is a noop if ArtifactCache.isStoreSupported() returns false.
